When I tell you I have been a long time fan, I am being serious.  I lived in Las Vegas from 2003-2012.  This was a weekly visit shop for me.  Not even kidding.  When I moved back to Chicago, people always ask, do you miss Vegas?  and i used to say, "No, but I miss Capriottis!!!!"  Now there is one in Chicago.  And although I may only get to the city about 3 times a year, I drop some money in there to bring them home to share with friends and family (I live in Aurora) The last two times i went I was severely saddened by the quality of the Sammys.  I ordered a medium Bobby (MY FAVORITE) and you would think there was a turkey shortage.  There was not enough turkey on my sandwich to even make a bite if i took it all off.  I was saddened by this.  I'm paying almost $10 for a sandwich (and i dont mind) and I cant even see the meat.  That happened 2 times now.  That is just BS.  I didnt notice till I was home (1 hour away) and then what??  call them?  what are they gonna do?  I would seriously let people know through this review that the ORIGINAL LOCATIONS IN LAS VEGAS DO IT RIGHT.  You cant even get your mouth around the sammy out there.  So if you are a fan of Delicious Capriotti's now, just imagine if they made them like they were intended to be made.  Sadly disappointed.  I may have to divorce this place.  VERY SAD DAY.

Will definitely be back 💯

Capriotti’s Wow. I love Thanksgiving food. So much so that I would eat it in a sandwich. And that’s exactly what I did here at Capriotti’s. Their sandwich called the Bobbie has turkey, stuffing, and cranberry sauce all jammed into a thick roll. Awesome sandwich, and while I may not be so sure they’re the “best sandwich in america” as stated on their bag, I would be hard pressed to argue that this was the best sub sandwich that I can recall ever having in my life.
